                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4812: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-08T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 8, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>459. Legation’s 455, July 6. No trains have arrived or left since July 5th. I am
                    reliably though not officially informed that about 3 kilometers of the railway
                    line were destroyed by an Abyssinian band this side of Mojo and killing Italian
                    guard of 40 men at Addas some 25 miles from here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
